Nyeri Senate Jubilee nominee Ephraim Maina has urged the IEBC to disqualify aspirants who destroy his billboards. He said despite conducting peaceful campaigns, his rivals have decided to use guerilla tactics to sabotage him. Maina spoke in Nyeri town on Tuesday. One of his billboards was destroyed on Monday night. He urged the police to investigate and ensure the culprits are brought to book. &ldquo;The IEBC should take disciplinary action against those who destroy my billboards. Also, the police should do their work,&rdquo; Maina said. Nyeri woman representative nominee Rahab Mukami urged rivals to desist from sabotage. Nyeri woman representative candidate Priscilla Nyokabi urged voters to reelect her so she can finish the projects she started. She will run as an independent.